An Act expanding reasons for excused absences from school to include mental or behavioral
health.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 1 of Chapter 76 of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2020
2 Official Edition, is hereby amended by inserting in line 25, after the words “any period of six
3 months”, the following:-
4 “, provided that a school shall excuse absences due to mental health symptoms in the
5 same manner that absences are excused for physical health symptoms. Likewise, any
6 requirement for documentation, either from a parent or health professional, shall be consistent
7 for absence due to mental health symptoms as for physical health symptoms. When
8 documentation is required of a healthcare professional, a school shall accept documentation from
9 licensed mental health care professionals in the same manner as documentation from other health
10 care professionals. A child who is absent due to mental or behavioral health shall be offered the
11 opportunity to meet with a certified school counselor upon return to school, but shall not be
12 required to do so.”
